.SH NAME
zopen-generate \- manual page for zopen-generate 0.8.5
.SH DESCRIPTION
zopen\-generate will generate a zopen compatible project
Syntax: zopen\-generate [options]
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-help\fR
Display this help message
.TP
\fB\-\-version\fR
Display version information
.TP
\fB\-\-list\-licenses\fR
List available licenses
.TP
\fB\-\-list\-categories\fR
List available categories
.TP
\fB\-\-list\-build\-systems\fR
List supported build systems
.TP
\fB\-\-name\fR NAME
Project name
.TP
\fB\-\-description\fR DESC
Project description
.TP
\fB\-\-categories\fR CATS
Project categories (space\-delimited)
.TP
\fB\-\-license\fR LICENSE
License name
.TP
\fB\-\-type\fR TYPE
Port type: 'BUILD' (from source) or 'BARE' (binary download)
.TP
\fB\-\-build\-system\fR SYSTEM
Build system if type is BUILD (GNU Make, CMake, Gradle, Maven, etc.)
.TP
\fB\-\-c\-extensions\fR
Python project contains C extensions (requires C compiler)
.TP
\fB\-\-stable\-url\fR URL
Stable release source URL (Git HTTPS clone URL ending in .git,
